{"id": "csi1665702634389", "title": "rollback", "breadcrumbs": ["Uniface Reference", "ProcScript Reference", "ProcScript: Statements", "rollback"], "url": "https://docs.rocketsoftware.com/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/csi1665702634389.html", "html": "<html><body><header class=\"zDocsTopicPageHead\"><h1 class=\"css-g931ng\">rollback</h1><div class=\"zDocsTopicActions\" role=\"list\"><div class=\"zDocsBundlePagination\" data-testid=\"next-prev-container\" role=\"listitem\"><div class=\"zDocsPrevTopicButton zDocsPrevTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Previous: returns \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Previous: returns \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eva1665702625026.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-prev\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-prev\"></use></svg></a></span></div><div class=\"zDocsNextTopicButton zDocsNextTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Next: run (deprecated)   \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Next: run (deprecated)   \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qiy1665703006046.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></a></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsMyDocsMenu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Add to My Topics\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Add to My Topics\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" id=\"addToMyDocsDropdownTrigger\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/csi1665702634389.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/csi1665702634389.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/csi1665702634389.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526595\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526595\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104csi1665702634389.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/csi1665702634389.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/csi1665702634389.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"csi1665702634389\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"csi1665702634389__rollback_237386\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Undo the transaction (if supported by DBMS).</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"csi1665702634389__topic_d76733e1_d76734e1_d76735e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"csi1665702634389__p_d76736e1_d76737e1_d76738e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PathString</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>}</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"csi1665702634389__topic_d50437e1_d50438e1_d50439e1_d50440e1_d50441e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1042123e74\">Parameters</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7310e1_d7311e1_d7312e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7310e1_d7311e1_d7312e1__entry__1\">\n Parameter\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7310e1_d7311e1_d7312e1__entry__2\">\n Data Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7310e1_d7311e1_d7312e1__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7310e1_d7311e1_d7312e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PathString</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7310e1_d7311e1_d7312e1__entry__2\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7310e1_d7311e1_d7312e1__entry__3\">\n Required path name. Can be a path name ($XXX) or DBMS path defined in the application model. If omitted, all updates made by the transaction to all DBMSs are rolled back. If the target DBMS does not support <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span>, this statement is ignored.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"csi1665702634389__topic_d50442e1_d50443e1_d50444e1_d50445e1_d50446e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1042123e131\">Return Values </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__2\">\n Data was successfully rolled back.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;0</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__2\">\n An error occurred. <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> contains the exact error.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-3</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__2\">\n Exceptional I/O error (hardware or software).\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-9</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__2\">\n An attempt to open a DBMS failed because the maximum number of DBMS logons has already been reached.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-16</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7313e1_d7314e1_d7315e1__entry__2\">\n Network error: unknown.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Values commonly returned by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> following\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Error constant\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-2</code> through <code class=\"ph codeph\">-12</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UIOSERR_*&gt;</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Errors during database I/O.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-16</code> through <code class=\"ph codeph\">-30</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UNETERR_*&gt;</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Errors during network I/O.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1107</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UPROCERR_PATH&gt;</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"csi1665702634389__table_d7316e1_d7317e1_d7318e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\">\n The path name is not correct or the path does not exist, for example, no assignment is found for the path.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"csi1665702634389__topic_d50447e1_d50448e1_d50449e1_d50450e1_d50451e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1042123e321\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"csi1665702634389__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"csi1665702634389__topic_d50452e1_d50453e1_d50454e1_d50455e1_d50456e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1042123e331\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"csi1665702634389__p_d76754e1_d76755e1_d76756e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> statement undoes all updates to the database made since the last <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> was issued (or since the application started or the path was opened), and unlocks all occurrences.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"csi1665702634389__p_d76757e1_d76758e1_d76759e1\">If <var class=\"keyword varname\">PathString</var> starts with a dollar sign (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$</span>), the argument is assumed to be a path name. Updates to all entities accessed through that path are rolled back. In this case, assignments determine which entities are rolled back.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"csi1665702634389__p_d76760e1_d76761e1_d76762e1\">Otherwise, the argument is assumed to be a DBMS path defined in the application model. Updates to all entities assigned to that DBMS are rolled back. In this case, the model definition determines which entities are rolled back.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"csi1665702634389__p_d76763e1_d76764e1_d76765e1\">This statement is usually used when a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> fails.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"csi1665702634389__p_d76766e1_d76767e1_d76768e1\">To avoid currency problems, use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> (or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span>) at the highest level of the component tree for the current transaction. For example, if Component B is activated by Component A, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> statement should be in Component A rather than Component B.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"csi1665702634389__fig_d76769e1_d76770e1_d76771e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Transaction Control at the Highest Level of the Component Tree</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Component A activates component B, which activates Component C. Ccomponent C returns -2 if $status=0. Component B returns -2. Component A issues rollback in response to $status=-2\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/transactioncontrolmultiplecomponents.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 1. Transaction Control at the Highest Level of the Component Tree\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/transactioncontrolmultiplecomponents.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"csi1665702634389__p_d76775e1_d76776e1_d76777e1\">However, if the component's <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Component Behavior</span> property is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Keep component definition and data in memory</code>\", you should use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> at that component's level.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"csi1665702634389__section_onm_jxl_zbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1042123e407\">Example: Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span></h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example uses <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> when a\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span> statement fails:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"csi1665702634389__pre_p51_rxl_zbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger store\n store\n if ($status &lt; 0)\n message \"Store error number %%$status.\"\n rollback\n else\n message \"Store done.\"\n commit\n endif\nend; store</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lnt1665702561005.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Transaction Control</a><p>A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpl1665702560927.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>commit</a><p>Commit a transaction to a DBMS or path.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kgi1665702560769.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>store</a><p>Initiate validation and storage of all occurrences marked as modified. It activates the appropriate validation triggers as required, followed by the write and delete triggers.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526595\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526595\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "rollback Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Undo the transaction (if supported by DBMS). rollback { \" PathString \" } Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description PathString String Required path name. Can be a path name ($XXX) or DBMS path defined in the application model. If omitted, all updates made by the transaction to all DBMSs are rolled back. If the target DBMS does not support rollback , this statement is ignored. Return Values Table 2. Values returned in $status Value Meaning 0 Data was successfully rolled back. <0 An error occurred. $procerror contains the exact error. -3 Exceptional I/O error (hardware or software). -9 An attempt to open a DBMS failed because the maximum number of DBMS logons has already been reached. -16 Network error: unknown. Table 3. Values commonly returned by $procerror following rollback Value Error constant Meaning -2 through -12 <UIOSERR_*> Errors during database I/O. -16 through -30 <UNETERR_*> Errors during network I/O. -1107 <UPROCERR_PATH> The path name is not correct or the path does not exist, for example, no assignment is found for the path. Use Allowed in all component types. Description The rollback statement undoes all updates to the database made since the last commit or rollback was issued (or since the application started or the path was opened), and unlocks all occurrences. If PathString starts with a dollar sign ( $ ), the argument is assumed to be a path name. Updates to all entities accessed through that path are rolled back. In this case, assignments determine which entities are rolled back. Otherwise, the argument is assumed to be a DBMS path defined in the application model. Updates to all entities assigned to that DBMS are rolled back. In this case, the model definition determines which entities are rolled back. This statement is usually used when a store or commit fails. To avoid currency problems, use rollback (or commit ) at the highest level of the component tree for the current transaction. For example, if Component B is activated by Component A, the rollback statement should be in Component A rather than Component B. Figure 1. Transaction Control at the Highest Level of the Component Tree However, if the component's Component Behavior property is set to Keep component definition and data in memory \", you should use commit at that component's level. Example: Using rollback The following example uses rollback when a store statement fails: trigger store store if ($status < 0) message \"Store error number %%$status.\" rollback else message \"Store done.\" commit endif end; store Copy Related Links Transaction Control A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction. commit Commit a transaction to a DBMS or path. store Initiate validation and storage of all occurrences marked as modified. It activates the appropriate validation triggers as required, followed by the write and delete triggers. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}